'''Chilled in a Field Festival''' is a small, family-friendly<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.festivalkidz.com/reviews/chilled-in-a-field-2014-review/|title=Chilled in a Field 2014 Review|publisher=Festival Kidz|author=Naomi|date=28 August 2014|accessdate=16 May 2016}}</ref> [[music festival]] in the [[United Kingdom]]. First run in 2010,<ref name="totw">{{cite news|url=https://www.timesoftunbridgewells.co.uk/chilled-family-festival-to-put-hop-farm-back-on-music-map/|title=‘Chilled’ family festival to put Hop Farm back on music map|newspaper=Times of Tunbridge Wells|date=25 May 2016|accessdate=2 June 2016}}</ref> in 2014 it was listed by [[The Guardian]] as one of their ''Top 25 summer festivals for music and arts lovers, foodies and families'',<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2014/apr/11/summer-festivals-uk-europe-music-family|title=Top 25 summer festivals for music and arts lovers, foodies and families|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|first=Katie|last=Antoniou|date=11 April 2014|accessdate=16 May 2016}}</ref> and given a Gold Award by the family festival review website Festival Kidz.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.festivalkidz.com/blog/fk-award-winners-2014/|title=Festival Kidz Award Winners 2014|author=Naomi|publisher=Festival Kidz|date=1 January 2015|accessdate=16 May 2016}}</ref> The festival now draws an attendance of 1,500+,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theargus.co.uk/leisure/critic/13526008.Review__Chilled_in_a_Field_at_Bentley_Wildfowl_and_Motor_Museum/|title=Review: Chilled in a Field at Bentley Wildfowl and Motor Museum|first=Tom|last=Locke|newspaper=[[The Argus (Brighton)]]|date=3 August 2015|accessdate=16 May 2016}}</ref> having grown from an attendance of only 120 people in its first year.<ref name="totw" />

The festival was first held in [[Hawkhurst]], [[Kent]],<ref name="totw" /> and has also been held at [[The Hop Farm Country Park]] in [[Paddock Wood]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehopfarm.co.uk/events/chilled-in-a-field-festival|title=Chilled in a Field Festival - The Hop Farm|year=2015|publisher=The Hop Farm|accessdate=16 May 2016}}</ref> and at Bentley Wildfowl and Motor Museum in Sussex. Bands headlining the festival have included [[The Egg (band)|The Egg]], [[Cocos Lovers]], and [[Tankus the Henge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chilledinafieldfestival.co.uk/live-music.html|title=Live music at Chilled in a Field|publisher=Chilled in a Field Festival|year=2016|accessdate=16 May 2016}}</ref> The festival was again held in 2018 and will return in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chilledinafieldfestival.co.uk/l|title=Chilled in a Field Festival|publisher=Chilled in a Field Festival|year=2016|accessdate=3 August 2016}}</ref>

